comments.message:
We should test `repo->first == record` first right? As it is not expensive at all, unlike `pldm_pdr_get_prev_record()` which is `O(N)` wrt the repository size.

so:

```
if (repo->first == record) {
    return true;
}

return pldm_pdr_get_prev_record(repo, record) != NULL;
```

Given we're skipping it we can avoid testing the result, but we do need to test the result of the `hdr_type` extraction below. So this could instead look like:

```
pldm_msgbuf_span_required(dst, skip_data_size, NULL);
if ((rc = pldm_msgbuf_extract(dst, hdr_type))) {
   return rc;
}
```

That should save the awkward wrapping of the `NULL` parameter.

We can save a bit of noise here and write it as:

```
pldm_msgbuf_span_required(dst, skip_data_size, NULL);
if ((rc = pldm_msgbuf_extract(dst, hdr_type))) {
    return rc;
}
```

If we're jumping out to cleanup in this case then there's no need to encase the rest in the `} else {` block below. It should be:

```
if (!match) {
    goto cleanup;
}

*record_handle = record->record_handle;
prev = pldm_pdr_get_prev_record(repo, record);
return pldm_pdr_remove_record(repo, record, prev);
```

Note that we can return the result of `pldm_pdr_remove_record()` directly. We can do this because we tested the results of the extraction above on line 2018 (that is, we already know all the information that will be given to us by `pldm_msgbuf_destroy()`). We've also hit the condition we were trying to match, so there's no more work to do. Therefore we can just return directly.

I realise I've bikeshedded this a bit, but perhaps we invert the test:

```
...
if (match) {
    *record_handle = record->record_handle;
    prev = pldm_pdr_get_prev_record(repo, record);
    return pldm_pdr_remove_record(repo, record, prev);
}
...
```

Looking at this more closely, I think this condition comes up short. Looking at your implementation of `pldm_pdr_record_matches_fru_rsi()` it can return a negative errno value, as well as either 0 or 1.

I think you need:

```
match = pldm_pdr_record_matches_fru_rsi(...);
if (match < 0) {
    return match;
}

if (match) {
    ...
}
```

Definitions should be at the top of the function, before any code.

You need to split the definition from the assignment for `record`:

```
static const skip_data_size = sizeof(uint32_t) + sizeof(uint8_t);
pldm_pdr_record *record;
pldm_pdr_record *pref;
uint8_t hdr_type;
int match;
int rc;

if (!repo || !record_handle) {
    return -EINVAL;
}

record = repo->first;
```
